I've been growing fresh sprouts in my kitchen for a year now! I get asked about them all the time. So I made a video explaining how I do it! It's easy, fun, super healthy, cheap, and YOU SHOULD START DOING IT TOO!

You just need some sprouts grade seeds, jars, and mesh lids to get started. I'd also recommend some metal stands. You can find all that on amazon.com by searching "sprout growing kits" 

In the US, I like buying my seeds from trueleafmarket.com you can also get supplies there too. A good seed to start with is Todd's seed mix "Broccoli and friends" from toddsseeds.com

More information can be found by Google searching "how to grow sprouts in jars" or you can buy a book. I liked Doug Evans book, "The Sprout Book"
